#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.74"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.74:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.74:0.2"
msgid "8. Ānandavagga"
msgstr "8. Ānanda"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.74:0.3"
msgid "74. Nigaṇṭhasutta"
msgstr "74. Jains"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.221"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.74:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in "
"the hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "an3.74:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho abhayo ca licchavi paṇḍitakumārako ca licchavi yenāyasmā ānando "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho abhayo licchavi āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Licchavis Abhaya and Paṇḍitakumāra went up to Venerable Ānanda, "
"bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

#. VAR: nāṭaputto → nātaputto (bj) | nāthaputto (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.74:1.3"
msgid ""
"“nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ "
"paṭijānāti:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the Jain leader Nāṭaputta claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to "
"know and see everything without exception, thus:"

msgctxt "an3.74:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while "
"walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.’"

msgctxt "an3.74:1.5"
msgid ""
"So purāṇānaṃ kammānaṃ tapasā byantībhāvaṃ paññāpeti navānaṃ kammānaṃ akaraṇā "
"setughātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"He advocates the elimination of past karma by mortification, and breaking "
"the bridge by not making new karma."

# this appears to be future perfect, https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/the-future-perfect-tense-in-pali/4630/20
msgctxt "an3.74:1.6"
msgid ""
"Iti kammakkhayā dukkhakkhayo, dukkhakkhayā vedanākkhayo, vedanākkhayā sabbaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ bhavissati—"
msgstr ""
"So with the ending of karma, suffering ends; with the ending of suffering, "
"feeling ends; and with the ending of feeling, all suffering will have been "
"worn away."

# Note how this parallels: Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti
msgctxt "an3.74:1.7"
msgid "evametissā sandiṭṭhikāya nijjarāya visuddhiyā samatikkamo hoti."
msgstr ""
"This is how to go beyond suffering by means of this purification by wearing "
"away in this very life."

msgctxt "an3.74:1.8"
msgid "Idha, bhante, bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What, sir, does the Buddha say about this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.74:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Tisso kho imā, abhaya, nijjarā visuddhiyo tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā "
"arahatā sammāsambuddhena sammadakkhātā sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ "
"samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"“Abhaya, these three kinds of purification by wearing away have been rightly "
"explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the "
"fully awakened Buddha. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get "
"past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the "
"procedure, and to realize extinguishment."

msgctxt "an3.74:2.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.74:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, abhaya, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, Abhaya, a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of "
"conduct, and has appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing "
"danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an3.74:2.4"
msgid ""
"So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by "
"experiencing their results little by little."

msgctxt "an3.74:2.5"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā "
"viññūhīti."
msgstr ""
"This wearing away is realizable in this very life, immediately effective, "
"inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for "
"themselves."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.74:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, abhaya, bhikkhu evaṃ sīlasampanno vivicceva kāmehi … pe … "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Then a mendicant accomplished in ethics, quite secluded from sensual "
"pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the "
"first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption."

msgctxt "an3.74:3.2"
msgid ""
"So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by "
"experiencing their results little by little."

msgctxt "an3.74:3.3"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā "
"viññūhīti."
msgstr ""
"This wearing away is realizable in this very life, immediately effective, "
"inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for "
"themselves."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: evaṃ samādhisampanno → evaṃ sīlasampanno evaṃ samādhisampanno (bj, s1-3, km) | evaṃ sīlasampanno …pe… (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.74:4.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, abhaya, bhikkhu evaṃ samādhisampanno āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Then a mendicant accomplished in immersion realizes the undefiled freedom of "
"heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized "
"it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an3.74:4.2"
msgid ""
"So navañca kammaṃ na karoti, purāṇañca kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkaroti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t perform any new deeds, and old deeds are eliminated by "
"experiencing their results little by little."

msgctxt "an3.74:4.3"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhikā nijjarā akālikā ehipassikā opaneyyikā paccattaṃ veditabbā "
"viññūhīti."
msgstr ""
"This wearing away is realizable in this very life, immediately effective, "
"inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for "
"themselves."

msgctxt "an3.74:4.4"
msgid ""
"Imā kho, abhaya, tisso nijjarā visuddhiyo tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā "
"arahatā sammāsambuddhena sammadakkhātā sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ "
"samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the three kinds of purification by wearing away that have been "
"rightly explained by the Buddha … in order to realize extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.222"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.74:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, paṇḍitakumārako licchavi abhayaṃ licchaviṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Paṇḍitakumāra said to Abhaya:"

msgctxt "an3.74:5.2"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ pana tvaṃ, samma abhaya, āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitaṃ subhāsitato "
"nābbhanumodasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Dear Abhaya, is there anything in what Ānanda has said so well that you "
"would disagree with?”"

msgctxt "an3.74:5.3"
msgid ""
"“Kyāhaṃ, samma paṇḍitakumāraka, āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitaṃ subhāsitato "
"nābbhanumodissāmi."
msgstr "“How could I not agree with what was said so well by Ānanda?"

msgctxt "an3.74:5.4"
msgid ""
"Muddhāpi tassa vipateyya yo āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitaṃ subhāsitato "
"nābbhanumodeyyā”ti."
msgstr "If anyone didn’t agree with him, their head would explode!”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.74:5.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
